In [ ]:
inertias = []

phi = list(df.phi)
psi = list(df.psi)

angles = [list(a) for a in zip(phi, psi)]

for i in range(1, 7):
    n_clusters = i

    kmean = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters = n_clusters, random_state = 0).fit(angles)

    inertias.append(kmean.inertia_)

    centers = kmean.cluster_centers_
    labels = kmean.labels_
    
    l, all = [list(a) for a in zip(*sorted(zip(labels, angles)))]    
    all = np.array(all)

        
    plt.xlabel("phi [degrees]")
    plt.ylabel("psi [degrees]")
    start = 0
    stop = -1
    for i in range(n_clusters):
        try:
            stop = l.index(i + 1)
        except ValueError:
            stop = -1

        plt.scatter(all[start:stop, 0], all[start:stop, 1])
        start = stop


    for i in range(n_clusters):
        plt.plot(centers[i][0], centers[i][1], 'mo', ms = 7)

    plt.text(120, 140, r"$K = $" + str(n_clusters), bbox = {'facecolor': 'red', 'alpha': 0.5, 'pad': 5})
    plt.xlim([-180, 180])
    plt.ylim([-180, 180])
    plt.show()

plt.title("Elbow graph")
plt.ylabel("Inertia")
plt.xlabel("Number of clusters")
plt.plot(list(range(1, 7)), inertias)
plt.show()
In [ ]:
#shift all angles so periodic wrap happens in area with few points 

psi_shifted = df.psi.apply(lambda x: (x + 100) % 360)
phi_shifted = df.phi.apply(lambda x: x % 360)

shifted_angles = [list(a) for a in zip(phi_shifted, psi_shifted)]

inertias = []

for i in range(1, 7):
    n_clusters = i

    kmean = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters = n_clusters, random_state = 0).fit(shifted_angles)

    inertias.append(kmean.inertia_)
    centers = kmean.cluster_centers_
    labels = kmean.labels_

    l, all = [list(a) for a in zip(*sorted(zip(labels, shifted_angles)))]    
    all = np.array(all)
        

    start = 0
    stop = -1
    for i in range(n_clusters):
        try:
            stop = l.index(i + 1)
        except ValueError:
            stop = -1

        plt.scatter(all[start:stop, 0], all[start:stop, 1])
        start = stop

    for j in range(n_clusters):
        plt.plot(centers[j][0], centers[j][1], 'mo', ms = 7)

    plt.text(300, 320, r"$K = $" + str(n_clusters), bbox = {'facecolor': 'red', 'alpha': 0.5, 'pad': 5})
    plt.xlabel("phi [degrees]")
    plt.ylabel("psi [degrees]")
    plt.xlim([-10, 360])
    plt.ylim([-10, 360])
    plt.title("Shifted clustering")
    plt.show()

plt.title("Elbow graph")
plt.ylabel("Inertia")
plt.xlabel("Number of clusters")
plt.plot(list(range(1, 7)), inertias)
plt.show()

#DB SCAN
for i in range(4):
    min_samples = 40 + 30*i
    eps = 10 + 5*i
    
    dbscan = cluster.DBSCAN(min_samples=min_samples, eps=eps).fit(shifted_angles)

    labels = dbscan.labels_

    df["label"] = labels
    
    outliers_grouped = df[df.label == - 1].groupby(["residue name"]).size()
    print()
    for a in df["residue name"]:
        if a not in outliers_grouped:
            outliers_grouped.loc[a] = 0

    plt.bar(outliers_grouped.index , height=(outliers_grouped.values/df.groupby(["residue name"]).size())*100)
    plt.xticks(rotation = 45)
    plt.title("Outliers by residue")
    plt.xlabel("Residue")
    plt.ylabel("Percentage of group that are outliers")
    plt.show()

    l, all = [list(a) for a in zip(*sorted(zip(labels, shifted_angles)))]
    n_clusters = l[-1] + 1

    all = np.array(all)
    outliers = l.index(0)
    
    start = 0
    stop = -1
    
    marker = None
    color = None
    if l[0] == -1:    
        marker = 'x'
        color = 'k'


    for i in range(n_clusters + 1):
        try:
            stop = l.index(i)
        except ValueError:
            stop = -1

        plt.scatter(all[start:stop, 0], all[start:stop, 1], marker = marker, c = color )
        marker = None
        color = None
        start = stop

    plt.text(50, -100, f"Min samples = {min_samples}, Eps = {eps}, Outliers = {outliers}", bbox = {'facecolor': 'red', 'alpha': 0.5, 'pad': 5})
    plt.xlim([-10, 360])
    plt.ylim([-10, 360])
    plt.title("Shifted clustering, DBscan")
    plt.xlabel("phi [degrees], shifted")
    plt.ylabel("psi [degrees], shifted")
    plt.show()
